projectDescription: This web-based project was developed to predict sales using technologies such as React, Material UI, Node.js, Express, and MySQL. It was created for a final thesis and applies the Weighted Moving Average and Single Exponential Smoothing methods for forecasting. The system uses Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE) to evaluate prediction accuracy. It also manages product and sales data, and includes user authentication and authorization features to ensure secure access.

features.featureDescription: Predict future product sales using Weighted Moving Average and Single Exponential Smoothing methods.
Evaluate prediction accuracy using Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE).
Store and manage data for each product including name, category, and other relevant details.
Record and organize sales data for each product over time.
Allow users to register and log in securely using authentication mechanisms.

projectDescription: Omnifood is a fully responsive static website built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It presents a modern interface for a fictional food catering service, showcasing meal plans, service benefits, and customer testimonials. Although it does not include backend functionality, the website is designed to provide a smooth user experience across all devices, focusing on clean design and accessibility.

A backend project built using Java, Spring Framework, and MySQL, created as a learning initiative to explore Spring and Java development. The API comes with comprehensive documentation and connects to a MySQL database to manage data related to Users, Contacts, and Addresses.

A simple landing page project about data management, built using React and Tailwind CSS. This project was created as a learning exercise to practice building responsive UI layouts with modern frontend technologies. It features a clean, analytics-themed design, focusing on layout, styling, and component structure.

A social media app project built with React, Material UI, Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. This project was created as a learning experience to explore full-stack web development. It allows users to perform basic social media interactions while practicing frontend and backend integration, RESTful APIs, and database management.

An admin dashboard project developed using React, Material UI, Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. This project was built to learn full-stack development by creating a functional interface for managing data. It includes features like data visualization, user management, and API integration with a MongoDB backend.

A hotel room booking website developed using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap 5, Python, Flask, and MySQL. This project focuses on implementing the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture using Flask to separate concerns between data, logic, and UI. It allows users to view, book, and manage hotel rooms while practicing backend development and database integration.

A book borrowing website for Gramedia, developed using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap 5, Python, Flask, and MySQL. This project focuses on implementing the MVC pattern with Flask, allowing users to view available books, borrow them, and manage borrowing records. It was created as a learning platform to practice web development and database integration.

A car catalog application developed for Android using Java, with a PHP backend and MySQL database. This project focuses on displaying car data fetched from a remote server, created as a learning experience in building Android apps that consume API data.

Genshin Wiki is an Android application built using Java, with a PHP backend and MySQL database. It serves as a simple wiki app for the game Genshin Impact, displaying character and item data. This project was created to practice Android development and API integration for presenting game-related information.
